<br>
It was yesterday when I decided to join Finrael and Meriel for a visit in the dungeon Befallen. We got there with no problems while travelling, though I had some small dealing with those large dunes in Northern Desert of Ro <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Once we entered the foul undead dungeon we quickly moved to the 2nd floor, since Fin already had a key for this 1st locked door. The undead minions could not stand a chance vs us cleaning the rooms on 2nd floor one by one. We then reached the so called pit and checked the trap which was 'hidden' <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  there, which dropped us onto the 3rd floor. That was the time when things changed to get worse...we quickly realized that we would need another key for that door to safety, but no one of us had it. While we were considering what to do next and calling poeple for a little help we had to fight much tougher skeletons which forced us to be really watchful. It was while we we resting from such a fight when we realized that an elven skeleton had appeared directly at the only door to exit, it seemed to be very tough and the ghoul next to it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  wouldn't be of much help either, that we knew.<br>
So we were not feeling very well down there, knowing that there is a door for which we don't have a key and some nasty undead guarding it as well. <br>
<br>
This first picture I took shows us three standing at the opposite side wall of the hallway, more hiding than fighting <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.wtal.de/madman/befallen1.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
But then all of a sudden a rogue named Stele came throught one of the doors down there and engaged the elven skel while we attacked the ghoul. He was very nice and opened the door for us, I'd bet he had no key himself but since he's a rogue, hehe.<br>
So now we were back in the game, just taking a short break for selling the loot we got so far. Gorte had arrived at the entrance, he had intended to help us down there in our trap, what we really all appreciated.<br>
When we were ready to move to 2nd floor again we added Varigon and Maitlin to our party, which were already in Befallen before to heal and help the poeple who fought on 1st floor. A very well experienced halfling druid named Quiv blessed our whole group with a skin like nature spell and the powerful nature regeneration spell cloroplast. Needless to say that we felt like small gods after that, now that we were close to invincible <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
We rushed throught the 2nd floor killing every undead being and those nasty necros and shadowknights had not even the slightest chance to beat us.<br>
The next pictures I took show us while in this battle rage...<br>
<br>
Here we see on of the rooms almost cleared with only one poor skel left but soon to be beaten as well.<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.wtal.de/madman/befallen2.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Here another room with the three paladins of our group splintering every single undead bone.<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.wtal.de/madman/befallen3.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
And last but not least we reached the room in which we encountered the big, fat and mean ogre shadowknight...well, as you see he was not really able to harm us <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.wtal.de/madman/befallen4.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Sadly Finrael had to leave soon after that, but we others stayed in there for the rest of the night. The druid buffing was already gone but we still rocked the entire 2nd floor and though it got more critical a few times, since those shadowknights ran away from us (haha <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) and brought many of their friends with them, we still all survived. I hope the caster or mixed type classes don't mind us Paladins always rushing for the next target while they were still meddin, it just was too addictive <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Altogether I really had a blast yesterday and I want to thank everyone who was in this great group....Meriel (ladies first *g*), Finrael, Gorte, Maitlin and Varigon (who I both would really like to see in our guild soon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
But after this fight night I also appreciate the upcoming fishing and celebrating today, see ya all there...<br>
<br>
 <p>Farewell !!<br>
